## SSL/TLS Certificates

### Production Certificate (Let's Encrypt - ACTIVE)
```bash
# Let's Encrypt Certificate Paths
export SSL_CERT_PATH="/etc/letsencrypt/live/aurcrt/fullchain.pem"
export SSL_KEY_PATH="/etc/letsencrypt/live/aurcrt/privkey.pem"
export SSL_CHAIN_PATH="/etc/letsencrypt/live/aurcrt/chain.pem"

# NGINX SSL Directory (container)
export NGINX_SSL_DIR="/etc/nginx/ssl"

# Certificate Authority
export CA_CERT_PATH="/etc/ssl/certs/ca-certificates.crt"

# Certificate Details
export SSL_DOMAIN="aurcrt"
export SSL_CERT_EXPIRY="2025-12-03"
export SSL_CERT_ISSUED="2025-09-04"
export SSL_AUTO_RENEWAL="enabled"
```

### Fallback Certificate (Self-signed - DEVELOPMENT ONLY)
```bash
# Self-signed Certificate Paths
export FALLBACK_CERT_PATH="/opt/DLT/ssl/cert.pem"
export FALLBACK_KEY_PATH="/opt/DLT/ssl/key.pem"

# Fallback Details
export FALLBACK_CERT_EXPIRY="2026-11-19"
export FALLBACK_CERT_TYPE="Self-signed X.509 (RSA 4096-bit)"
```

### TLS Configuration
```bash
# TLS Protocols and Ciphers
export TLS_PROTOCOLS="TLSv1.2 TLSv1.3"
export TLS_CIPHERS="HIGH:!aNULL:!MD5"
export TLS_PREFER_SERVER_CIPHERS="on"
```

**Certificate Renewal (Auto-renewal):**
```bash
# Auto-renewal with certbot (Let's Encrypt)
sudo certbot renew --dry-run  # Test renewal first

# Force renewal if needed
sudo certbot renew --force-renewal

# Check renewal status
systemctl status certbot.timer

# View all certificates
sudo certbot certificates

# Manual renewal (if needed)
sudo certbot certonly --nginx -d aurcrt
```

**Certificate Deployment to NGINX:**
```bash
# Copy Let's Encrypt certificates to NGINX container
docker cp /etc/letsencrypt/live/aurcrt/fullchain.pem nginx-gateway:/etc/nginx/ssl/
docker cp /etc/letsencrypt/live/aurcrt/privkey.pem nginx-gateway:/etc/nginx/ssl/

# Verify permissions
docker exec nginx-gateway ls -lh /etc/nginx/ssl/

# Test NGINX configuration
docker exec nginx-gateway nginx -t

# Reload NGINX (no downtime)
docker exec nginx-gateway nginx -s reload
```

**Certificate Monitoring:**
```bash
# Check certificate expiry dates
openssl x509 -in /etc/letsencrypt/live/aurcrt/fullchain.pem -noout -dates

# Verify certificate chain
openssl verify -CAfile /etc/letsencrypt/live/aurcrt/chain.pem \
  /etc/letsencrypt/live/aurcrt/fullchain.pem

# Check NGINX certificate in container
docker exec nginx-gateway cat /etc/nginx/ssl/fullchain.pem | openssl x509 -text -noout
```

**Alert Configuration:**
- Alert Threshold: 30 days before expiry (November 3, 2025)
- Primary Alert: Email from certbot
- Renewal Deadline: By November 3, 2025 (30 days before Dec 3 expiry)

